  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\n`TestAgent_Session_TTY_MOTD_Update` flakes intermittently under `-race` in CI ([coder/internal#1417](https://github.com/coder/internal/issues/1417)). Failing subtests show `(unknown)` duration, meaning the test binary was killed by timeout. No race detector warnings or assertion failures were captured.\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\n\r\nThe test used a 5ms `ServiceBannerRefreshInterval`, which under the race detector (~10x overhead) created:\r\n- **200 DRPC calls/second**, each creating a new connection (PipeConns), acquiring FakeAgentAPI's mutex, serializing protobuf, and tearing down\r\n- **Heavy mutex contention** on the single `sync.Mutex` in FakeAgentAPI (30+ lock sites across all methods)\r\n- **~5-20% CPU** just for banner polling, starving the SSH session I/O pipeline\r\n\r\nThe session I/O chain (ptytest -> SSH client -> tailnet -> SSH server -> PTY -> shell) requires multiple goroutine handoffs, all slower under `-race`. Combined with the polling contention, this caused `session.Wait()` to hang until the Go test timeout killed the binary.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, the bare `<-ready` channel receives had no timeout, so if `fetchServiceBannerLoop` exited with an error (possible under DRPC contention), the test would hang silently.\r\n\r\n## Fix\r\n\r\n1. **Increase refresh interval** from 5ms to `testutil.IntervalFast` (25ms), reducing DRPC connection churn and mutex contention by 5x\r\n2. **Replace bare `<-ready`** with `testutil.TryReceive(ctx, t, ready)` to fail with context expiry instead of hanging indefinitely\r\n3. **Add timeout to `session.Wait()`** in `testSessionOutput` to prevent any SSH session hang from killing the entire test binary\r\n\r\n> \ud83e\udd16 This PR was created with the help of Coder Agents, and has been reviewed by a human. \ud83c\udfc2\ud83c\udffb",
